# Java Testing Conventions

## Framework

JUnit 5 + Mockito + AssertJ

## Class Setup

```java
@ExtendWith(MockitoExtension.class)
class MyServiceImplTest {
    @Mock private MyDao myDao;
    @InjectMocks private MyServiceImpl service;
}
```

## Method Naming

Use `should*` pattern: `shouldThrowExceptionIfInteractionAlreadyPresent`, `shouldReturnEmptyListWhenNoResults`

## Grouping

Use `@Nested` classes for logical groups:

```java
@Nested
class CreateInteraction {
    @Test void shouldCreateSuccessfully() { ... }
    @Test void shouldRejectDuplicateName() { ... }
}
```

## Assertions

- Prefer AssertJ: `assertThat(result).usingRecursiveComparison().isEqualTo(expected)`
- For RxJava: use `.test()` to get `TestObserver`, then `assertValue()`, `assertError()`

## Coverage

- JaCoCo enforced: **35% overall**, **80% on changed files**
- Focus tests on service and DAO layers
